Karen Gaynor appeared at Rotherham Magistrates Court accused of causing criminal damage by pruning a tree in her garden . 
  She was locked in a police cell for six hours and put on bail for seven months . 
  Magistrates took just 15 minutes to find her not guilty of the charge . 
  Council officials told her she could trim the tree but refused to show her how . 
  Neighbour Kay Daye complained about the hedge as part of a boundary dispute . 
  Ms Gaynor was accused of criminal damage and was put on trial . 
 